    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2003 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant mated to a G96 6-speed manual transaxle. This naturally aspirated unit utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing, delivering a linear 320 hp to the rear wheels. This example has been properly maintained with an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent water pump replacement. The suspension geometry remains true, providing the communicative feedback inherent to the 996 chassis. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the engine exhibits strong compression and the synchros remain crisp across all gear sets. Ideal for the purist seeking a visceral, analog driving experience with the peace of mind of addressed mechanical vulnerabilities.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 49
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
